nal metadata in the process. It feels like there might be an expectation to address both aspects to ensure a comprehensive review. Let's make sure I’m looking at all angles before proceeding!\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"text\", \"text\": \"Implemented a dedicated Kotlin test for the active dynamic-access class.\\n\\nChanged:\\n- Added `tests/src/org.jetbrains.kotlin/kotlin-scripting-jvm/2.3.21/src/test/kotlin/org_jetbrains_kotlin/kotlin_scripting_jvm/KJvmCompiledScriptDataTest.kt`\\n\\nWhat it covers:\\n- Constructs a public `KJvmCompiledScript`, which owns the internal `KJvmCompiledScriptData`.\\n- Serializes it with `ObjectOutputStream`, reaching all `KJvmCompiledScriptData.writeObject(...)` call sites.\\n- Deserializes it with `ObjectInputStream`, reaching all `KJvmCompiledScriptData.readObject(...)` call sites.\\n- Verifies restored script data through public API accessors.\\n\\nI did not run or compile tests, per instruction.\", \"textSignature\": \"{\\\"v\\\":1,\\\"id\\\":\\\"msg_0879ef3d4eccd5020169f903de2c60819789676a0806ea3776\\\",\\\"phase\\\":\\\"final_answer\\\"}\"}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 929, \"output\": 995, \"cacheRead\": 39424, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 41348, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"stop\", \"timestamp\": 1777927122094, \"responseId\": \"resp_0879ef3d4eccd5020169f903d334508197a4c8e586b53b144f\"}}\n/home/jovan/Work/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.jetbrains.kotlin:kotlin-scripting-jvm:2.3.21/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-04T20-38-55-440856Z.log:3194:[recv] {\"type\": \"turn_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering metadata tests**\\n\\nI'm thinking about the dynamic report, which focuses on metadata tests. Adding more tests could potentially uncover any missing metadata, but I won